The paper discusses the privacy concerns related to digital advertising and proposes a methodology for detecting cross-device tracking (CDT). This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with the protection of personal data from unauthorized access. Additionally, the paper involves the use of technology to emulate browsing activity and measure the impact of CDT on users, which could also be classified under cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and multimedia (cs.MM).
